This paper discusses the combination of reference capabilities and gradual typing, which are both topics in programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also addresses the issue of memory side-effects, which is a concern in software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to type checking, which is related to logic in computer science (cs.LO), and discusses the removal of data races, which is a security concern (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of type qualifiers, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC).
